This is a picture of me with my precious Carrie. She had a rough start in life. She was roaming the streets as a 3 month old starving puppy, with fleas and worms. But my son Ryan brought her home from a nearby park where he spotted her.  And for the next 13 years, she was my constant companion...whether I was jogging, inside at home, or outside working in our yard or at our ranch. As a golden retriever mix, she was extremely intelligent and sweet-tempered, and easy to train.  I still miss her terribly, even six years after she died.
You never not miss them.
Our rescue Abby is our treasure...we love her so much.
